// // Responsive: Utility classes // --------------------------------------------------
// IE10 in Windows (Phone) 8 // // Support for responsive views via media queries is kind of borked in IE10, for // Surface/desktop in split view and for Windows Phone 8. This particular fix // must be accompanied by a snippet of JavaScript to sniff the user agent and // apply some conditional CSS to *only* the Surface/desktop Windows 8. Look at // our Getting Started page for more information on this bug. // // For more information, see the following: // // Issue: https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap/issues/10497 // Docs: http://getbootstrap.com/getting-started/#browsers // Source: http://timkadlec.com/2012/10/ie10-snap-mode-and-responsive-design/
@-ms-viewport { width: device-width; }
